<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 94 / World Trade News: Italian power job in Lebanon
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BEIRUT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Italy's Ansaldo company has won a contract worth Dollars 720m to build two
450MW combined cycle power stations in Lebanon. The Italian government will
finance the project as part of a soft loan to Lebanon. Five international
consortia had submitted bids to build the two plants, one in the northern
Baddawi region and the second at Zahrani in south Lebanon.
