<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 94 / London Stock Exchange: VSEL alert
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVE THOMPSON, JOEL KIBAZO, JEFFREY BROWN and GEORGE HORSINGTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Nuclear submarine contractor VSEL soared 225 to 1,228p after its admission
that it had received a takeover approach. Traders pinpointed British
Aerospace and GEC as the bid frontrunners, and the talk in the market
suggested that a full blown auction could well be in the offing.
If the consensus among analysts is any guide, any possible opening bid could
be an all-share offer of around 1,350p a share. Both potential bidders found
ready sellers, with BAe tumbling 15 to 449p and GEC dipping 4 to 289p.
Vosper Thornycroft, another maritime defence contractor, shared in the
excitement, moving up 23 to 720p.
