<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 94 / World Stock Markets: Mexico further weakens
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Equities fell a further 1.7 per cent yesterday as nervous investors
continued to take profits on the back of Wednesday's political
assassination.
Traders said the Mexican Stock Exchange suffered another declining session
as no concrete motive for the killing of Mr Francisco Ruiz Massieu,
secretary-general of the ruling Institutional Revolutionary party, came to
light. Selling of Mexican blue chip ADRs on Wall Street also drove the
market down. The IPC index closed 47.31 points lower at 2,717.51, but volume
dropped to a moderate 90.3m shares, valued at 1.12bn new pesos.
Brazil
Sao Paulo rallied 3.1 per cent as domestic and foreign investors returned to
the market on bullish sentiment ahead of Brazil's presidential election on
Monday. The Bovespa index finished 1,655 ahead at 54,426.
</TEXT>
