<TEXT>
Panasonic, the electronics company, has designed what it believes to be the
first genuinely portable, multimedia PC.
The Panasonic CF-41 is a battery-operated, notebook PC with a CD-ROM (read
only computer memory stored on a compact disc) drive which weighs less than
8lbs. The notebook will be launched at the end of October costing between
Pounds 2,700 and Pounds 4,200.
