<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 94 / ScottishPower signs deal with Caledonian Paper
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JAMES BUXTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ScottishPower has signed a Pounds 40m four-year deal to supply electricity
to Caledonian Paper, the papermaker based at Irvine in Ayrshire, James
Buxton writes.
The companies have signed a partnership agreement aimed at co-operating to
achieve a 'fault-free' supply of electricity to the plant, which produces
200,000 tonnes of paper a year for magazines.
Caledonian Paper, part of Kymmene of Finland, has complained about the
quality of its electricity supply. Interruptions to the supply can halt
production, costing up to Pounds 100,000 a day in lost output.
ScottishPower has indicated that it will be able to supply power to
Caledonian Paper if the plant expands, as expected, in a few years.
</TEXT>
