<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 94 / Drop in business failures reported
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JIM KELLY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Business failures fell by 13.4 per cent in England and Wales in the first
nine months of this year, says Dun &amp; Bradstreet, the business information
group, Jim Kelly writes.
Figures released yesterday show that about 800 businesses failed each week
in that period, a total of 31,340. This compared with 36,203 in the same
period last year.
Mr Philip Mellor, senior analyst with the group, said that the figures
showed that the level of company liquidations was falling much faster - 17.7
per cent - than the level of bankruptcies - 10.5 per cent. He said: 'Larger
companies are in a much better position to take advantage of the recovery
while smaller businesses are less able to cope with the very competitive
business climate.'
Wales was the only area where failures increased, by 4 per cent, while the
west Midlands had the largest drop in England at 26.7 per cent.
</TEXT>
